events.name: GDG Cloud Tampere @ Gofore
events.description:
It's time for first ever GDG Cloud Tampere meetup! The event is hosted by Gofore.

Join us to influence how we are going to do meetups in the future and hear some tech talks. Also food and drinks will be provided.

Agenda:
18:00 Welcome and introductions
18:15 Word from our sponsor
18:30 Machine learning on Google Cloud - Johann du Toit
19:30 Kubernetes security - Jerry Jalava
20:30 Free mingling

events.name: GDG Cloud Tampere @ Eficode
events.description:
Welcome to the 2nd GDG Cloud Meetup at Eficode!

We learned something from our 1st meetup and decided that we should have a meetup dedicated for the basics. Even though you are familiar with the platform, there are still something to learn from actual customer cases and of course: socializing.

18:00 Doors are open, networking
18:10 Opening words - Tero Vepsäläinen
18:20 Word from the sponsor
18:30 GCP 101 - Jussi Kyröhonka (Google)
19:30 Motivation to use Kubernetes in Google Cloud - Toni Lahtinen (Gofore)
20:30 Why GCP & How to GCP Niklas Tanskanen (Eficode) and Alex Jantunen (Roidu)
21:30 Mingle
22:00 End of event

events.name: Cloud Study Jam - GCP Essentials
events.description:
GDG Cloud Tampere is organising Cloud Study Jam.

****READ THIS****
In our first Study Jam we are concentrating on beginners with GCP Essentials. So if you are already familiar with GCP this not for you, we will have other more advanced study jams later.

****KEEP READING****
At the event we’ll use a tool called Qwiklabs, a Google training product. If you have used Qwiklabs before, great! Make sure you know your password. If you have never used Qwiklabs before, save time by creating an account for yourself prior to the class at:
https://google.qwiklabs.com/users/sign_up

(creating an account is free).

At the event we will give you a link for free Qwiklabs access. Make sure you check the opt-in box for promos! That makes you eligible for additional free access after you complete the first series of labs.

****STILL KEEP READING****
What to bring to the event:
- Laptop -- Mac, PC, Chromebook, Linux, everyone’s welcome.
- Laptop charger.
- The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, use Firefox or Chrome.

Looking forward to seeing you at the event!

Schedule:

17:00 - Doors open & some snacks
17:30 - Study Jam Time
20:00 - Doors close

ps. places are very limited, so release your place if you can't make it.
pps. if this event is super popular we can run more GCP Essentials jams in the future.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam - Kubernetes in the Google Cloud
events.description:
*This is an introductory level session - so newcomers are very welcome.
We will eventually move to experienced sessions, if those are more in your ball park.*

Want to get started on the Google Cloud/Kubernetes, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam - Kubernetes in the Google Cloud!
Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console and Kubernetes.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

At the event we’ll use a tool called Qwiklabs, a Google training product. If you have used Qwiklabs before, great! Make sure you know your password. If you have never used Qwiklabs before, save time by creating an account for yourself prior to the class at:
https://google.qwiklabs.com/users/sign_up

(creating an account is free).

At the event we will give you a link for free Qwiklabs access. Make sure you check the opt-in box for promos! That makes you eligible for additional free access after you complete the first series of labs.

Thank you for reading this far, looking forward to seeing you all at the event!
PS. Don't forget your charger.

Agenda:
17:00: Welcome words
17:05: Sorting out Qwiklabs credentials
17:15: 3 Google Cloud Platform Kubernetes labs (Introduction to Docker, Kubernetes Engine: Qwik Start, Orchestrating the Cloud with Kubernetes)
18:30: Break (We will provide beverages and snacks)
19:00: Managing Deployments Using Kubernetes Engine
~20:00: Event ends (Can extend up to 21:00 if people want to mingle/ask questions.)

Spots are limited, so please if you can't make it update your attendance!

EDIT 19.06, what to do once you've found your seat etc:
1. https://go.qwiklabs.com/cloud-study-jams-2019
2. Enroll to: Kubernetes in the Google Cloud
3. Enter the study jam code: 1s-tampere-7676
